summary:
The Security Council:
Reaffirms its previous resolutions, particularly 696 (1991) and 1268 (1999);
Endorses the Secretary-General's decision to extend the UN Office in Angola's mandate for six months until 15 October 2000;
Requests the Secretary-General to continue implementing UNOA's tasks as outlined in resolution 1268 (1999);
Requests the Secretary-General to provide quarterly reports on developments in Angola, including recommendations on additional measures to promote the peace process;
Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
